@@TJvColorBox
##<TITLEIMG TJvColorBox>
##JVCLInfo
##  GROUP=JVCL.Graphics.Shapes, JVCL.PanelsBevelsAndGroups.Panels
##  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Displays the Windows standard colors as a set of 5x4 color squares.
Description
  Use TJvColorBox when you need to display the Windows standard colors in a control.
See Also
  TColorButton
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorBox.BorderStyle
Summary
  Determines the appearance of the control’s border.
Description
  Use BorderStyle to affect the visual appearance of the controls border. BorderStyle
  can have a value of either bsSingle or bsNone. If BorderStyle is bsSingle, the
  control has a single-line border around the client area. If BorderStyle is bsNone, there
  will be no border.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorBox.OnColorClick
Summary
  Occurs when one of the color squares are clicked by the user.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnColorClick event to take specific action when the user clicks on one of
  the color squares.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorClickEvent
<TITLE TJvColorClickEvent type>
Summary
  Type of event handlers that repsond to color square click events.
Description
  Use TJvColorClickEvent to respond to color square click events.
Parameters
  Sender - The object whose event handler is called.
  Button - The mouse button that was used to click the color square.
  Color  - The Color of the square
See Also
  TJvColorBox.OnColorClick, TJvColorSquare.OnColorClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorSquare
##<TITLEIMG TJvColorSquare>
##JVCLInfo
##  GROUP=JVCL.Graphics.Shapes
##  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A component that can display a color and optionally draw a frame around it's edge when the mouse hovers over it.
Description
  TJvColorSquare is used by the TJvColorBox and TJvColorButton to manage and display the individual colors
  in the color grids. To display a color in a window that also can highlight the current selection by
  drawing a special frame around the edge, use TJvColorSquare.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorSquare.BorderStyle
Summary
  Determines the appearance of the control’s border.
Description
  Use BorderStyle to affect the visual appearance of the controls border. BorderStyle
  can have a value of either bsSingle or bsNone. If BorderStyle is bsSingle, the
  control has a single-line border around the client area. If BorderStyle is bsNone, there
  will be no border.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorSquare.Color
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the control.
Description
  Use Color to read or change the background color of the control.

  If a control's ParentColor property is true, then changing the Color property of the control's
  parent automatically changes the Color property of the control. When the value of the
  Color property is changed, the control's ParentColor property is automatically set to false.
See Also
  ParentColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorSquare.OnChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color of the button changes.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnChange event to take specific action when the color of the control changes.
See Also
  OnColorClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorSquare.OnColorClick
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks on the square with the mouse.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnColorClick event to take specific action when the user clicks on
  the color squares using either mouse button.
See Also
  OnChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomDropButton
Summary
  A button that can display a drop-down arrow at the side of the button.
Description
  The TJvCustomDropButton is used as the basis for the TJvColorButton component. Derive a new control
  from TJvCustomDropButton when you need a button that can draw a drop-arrow and react to both
  button clicks as well as drop arrow clicks.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomDropButton.ArrowWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width of the arrow part of the button.
Description
  Use ArrowWidth to specify the width of the arrow part of the button. The arrow image will be
  sized accordingly.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomDropButton.DropDown
Summary
  Specifies a pop up menu that is used as the drop down for the arrow.
Description
  Use DropDown to assign a popup menu to use as the drop down menu for the button. When the user clicks
  the arrow part of the button, the menu is displayed below the button.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropButton
Summary
  A button that can display a drop-down arrow at the side of the button.
Description
  The TJvDropButton is used as the basis for the TJvColorButton component.
See Also
  TColorButton
